title: Red Arrows in the Night
creator: Daniel A. Lord
description: LibriVox recording of Red Arrows in the Night, by Daniel A. Lord. Read by Maria Therese. The Scarlet Archer of Agincourt is claimed by the Erkenwold’s as their family ghost. Tradition held that the death of an important Erkenwold was always heralded by the apparition of the Scarlet Archer. Now in the early years of WWII, the archer has made an appearance on the family estate on the US coast. Is it a ghost or something more sinister, and what does he or she want? This mystery novel was written by Daniel A Lord, S.J., who was a popular American Catholic writer. The subjects of the works in his bibliography range from religion, humor, plays, songs, mysteries and even politics. His most influential work was possibly in drafting the 1930 Production Code for motion pictures. (Introduction by Maria Therese and Wikipedia) M4B audiobook of complete book For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; fiction; horror/ghost stories; mystery
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: This was a good mystery, well read as a solo project by Maria Therese.  It's short, and doesn't get too deep into character development, but the action is quick and interesting and the ending was a surprise.

The summary pretty much covers the plot.  Easy to follow, interesting story, and a great ending.  Who could ask for more?  

Reader was excellent.
This is the second Father Lord book I've listened to. They are amusing little mysteries, perfect for a car ride. Marie Therese does a nice job of reading too.
